e of it.";i:5;s:55:"Meaning pronunciation translations and examples Log In.";i:6;s:28:"Define Chair of the Meeting.";i:7;s:98:"Means the chair of the meeting determined in accordance with the articles of incorporation of GBR.";i:8;s:80:"4 verb If you chair a meeting or a committee you are the person in charge of it.";i:9;s:66:"He was about to chair a meeting in Venice of EU foreign ministers.";i:10;s:37:"Definition in the dictionary English.";i:11;s:26:"Match all exact any words.";i:12;s:93:"In early December al-Bakri chaired a meeting of rebel leaders in the Ghouta village of Saqba.";i:13;s:118:"Health Canada chaired a meeting on April 11 2007 to discuss consumer information with key stakeholders including CPhA.";i:14;s:119:"In a more formal meeting the chairperson will outline the purpose of the meeting and remind members why they are there.";i:15;s:122:"In such a meeting there is little need to refer to this procedure as this is implicit in the established etiquette namely.";i:16;s:31:"The chair controls the meeting.";i:17;s:52:"A position of authority as of a judge professor etc.";i:18;s:78:"The person occupying a seat of office especially the chairperson of a meeting.";i:19;s:32:"The speaker addressed the chair.";i:20;s:58:"In an orchestra the position of a player assigned by rank.";i:21;s:120:"Committee chairs are responsible for facilitating committee meetings and reporting the committees findings to the board.";i:22;s:116:"Its essential for those who serve in the position of board chair to have a clear voice and good presentation skills.";i:23;s:30:"Define Chairperson of Meeting.";i:24;s:310:"Means the Chairman presiding over meetings of the Pradeshiya Sabha for the time being or the Vice Chairman of the Pradeshiya Sabha who takes the Chair in his absence and it also includes any other member elected on the vote of the members for the Chair in the absence of both the Chairman and the ViceChairman.";i:25;s:133:"To chair meeting translation in English - English Reverso dictionary see also charchairmanchaincharm examples definition conjugation.";i:26;s:115:"Therefore the individual should approach the chair of the committee and ask what their role in the meeting will be.";i:27;s:176:"For example if the meeting will involve proposing motions Proxy Vote A Proxy Vote is a delegation of voting authority to a representative on behalf of the original vote-holder.";i:28;s:112:"The party who receives the authority to vote is known as the Proxy and the original vote-holder is known as the.";i:29;s:24:"What does co-chair mean.";i:30;s:109:"To co chair is defined as to be jointly in charge of something such as planning an event with another person.";i:31;s:21:"What does chair mean.";i:32;s:33:"Bob will chair tomorrows meeting.";i:33;s:95:"To carry someone in a seated position upon ones shoulders especially in celebration or victory.";i:34;s:52:"Webster Dictionary 000 0 votes Rate this definition.";i:35;s:128:"The word chair can refer to the place from which the holder of the office presides whether on a chair at a lectern or elsewhere.";i:36;s:101:"During meetings the person presiding is said to be in the chair and is also referred to as the chair.";i:37;s:81:"A seat for one person that has a back usually four legs and sometimes two arms 2.";i:38;s:100:"Firstly a chairman is a presiding officer of a meeting and secondly of an organisation or committee.";i:39;s:124:"Every organisation or a committee has a chairman and he presides over all the meetings of the organisation or the committee.";i:40;s:105:"A chairman can be functionally defined as a person appointed to preside over a meeting and to conduct it.";i:41;s:68:"Chair - the officer who presides at the meetings of an organization.";i:42;s:179:"Address your remarks to the chairperson chairman chairperson chairwoman president Kalon Tripa - the chairman of the Kashag and essentially head of the Tibetan government-in-exile.";i:43;s:159:"2 The person in charge of a meeting or of an organization used as a neutral alternative to chairman or chairwoman a three-year term as the boards deputy chair.";i:44;s:75:"The princess is the chair of the sister organization in the United Kingdom.";i:45;s:134:"So the chair should be able to clearly define goals and be able to highlight that everyone has a stake in the success of a conference.";i:46;s:143:"Programme chair The programme chair ensures that a well-balanced high-quality technical programme is organized and presented at the conference.";i:47;s:25:"A chairman or chairwoman.";i:48;s:25:"A chairman or chairwoman.";i:49;s:32:"A person in charge of a meeting.";}}